<h1 id="xferlang-documentation">XferLang Documentation</h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p>XferLang is a data-interchange format designed to support data serialization, data transmission, and offline use cases such as configuration management.</p>
<pre><code class="language-xfer">{
    name &quot;Alice&quot;
    age 30
    isActive ~true
}
</code></pre>
<h2 id="design-philosophy">Design Philosophy</h2>
<p>XferLang is built around four core principles:</p>
<h3 id="clarity-and-readability">1. Clarity and Readability</h3>
<p>The syntax is designed to be human-readable without requiring separators like commas.</p>
<h3 id="explicit-typing">2. Explicit Typing</h3>
<p>All values are explicitly typed using prefixes.</p>
<h2 id="basic-syntax">Basic Syntax</h2>
<p>XferLang documents consist of elements separated by whitespace.</p>
<pre><code class="language-xfer">&lt;/ This is a comment /&gt;
name &quot;John Doe&quot;
age 30
</code></pre>
